obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (69596)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69596&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called "The Central Provinces Land-revenue Act, 1881":`
  line
  line `Local extent. It extends to all the territories for the time being under the administration of the Chief`
  line `Commissioner of the Central Provinces, except those specified in Part VI of the first schedule of the`
  line `Scheduled Districts Act 1874:`
  line
  line `Commencement. and it shall come into force on such day as the Chief Commissioner, with the`
  line `previous sanction of the Governor General in Council, may direct by notification in the local official`
  line Gazette.
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (69597)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Enactments repealed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69597&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `On and from such day the enactments mentioned in the schedule hereto`
  line `annexed, so far as they relate to the territories to which this Act extends, and all other rules, regulations and`
  line `enactments relating to the settlement and collection of the land-revenue in such territories, shall be repealed.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (69598)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Pending proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69598&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `All proceedings relating to matters dealt with by this Act and, when`
  line `this Act comes into force, pending before officers by whom they would be cognizable under this`
  line `Act, shall be deemed, so far as may be, to have been commenced hereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (69599)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Interpretation-clause.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69599&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is something repugnant in the subject or`
  line `context, —`
  line
  line `(1) “Assistant Commissioner” includes also “Extra Assistant Commissioner”:`
  line
  line `(2) “ Legal practitioner” means an advocate, vakil or attorney of any High Court, a pleader,`
  line `mukhtar or revenue-agent:`
  line
  line `(3) “Village-cess” means any cess which a person resident or holding lands in a village pays or`
  line `renders to the proprietors as such of the village, and includes service rendered or things furnished as`
  line `well as money paid:`
  line
  line `(4) “Recognized agent” means a person authorized in writing by any party to a proceeding under`
  line `this Act to make appearances and applications and to do other acts on his behalf in such proceeding and`
  line `also belonging to any class which the Chief Commissioner may, from time to time, by notification in`
  line `the official Gazette, declare in this behalf:`
  line
  line `(5) “Agricultural year means the year commencing on the first day of June, or on such other date`
  line `as the Chief Commissioner may, in the case of any specified district or districts, from time to time,`
  line `appoint:`
  line
  line `(6) “ Sir-land” means (a) land recorded as “sir” in the papers of the last preceding settlement of the`
  line `local area in which such land is situate; and (b) land not so recorded, but which has been cultivated by`
  line `the proprietor or one of the proprietors thereof for a period of not less than twelve consecutive years;`
  line `and (c) waste land which has been broken up by the proprietor or one of the proprietors thereof and`
  line `cultivated by him for a period of not less than six consecutive years; and (d) in Sambalpur, includes`
  line `also “ bhogra” land.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—Land which has, after the date of such settlement, or the expiry of such period of`
  line `twelve years, or six years (as the case may be), been for a period of six consecutive years unoccupied`
  line `by such proprietor is not sir-land. Land is not unoccupied by the proprietor when it is leased out by him`
  line `with an express reservation of his sir-rights:`
  line
  line `(7) “Mahal” means any local area held under a separate engagement for the payment of the`
  line `land-revenue direct to Government, and Includes also any local area declared, under the provisions of`
  line `this Act, to be a mahal:`
  line
  line `(8) “Village” includes any tract of land which, at the last settlement of such land, has been`
  line `recognized as a village, or which the Chief Commissioner may, from time to time, declare to be a`
  line `village for the purposes of this Act:`
  line
  line `(9) “Malguzar” means a person who, under the provisions of this Act, has accepted, or is to be`
  line `deemed to have accepted, the assessment of a mahal, and includes his representatives and assigns; and`
  line `also any person with whom a settlement has been made before this Act comes into force, and his`
  line `representatives and assigns:`
  line
  line `(10) “Malik-makbuza” means any person owning one or more plots of land assessed with revenue`
  line `in a mahal; but it does not include a malguzar or inferior proprietor:`
  line
  line `(11) “Lambardar” means a person appointed in manner prescribed by this Act to represent the`
  line `proprietary body of a mahal in its relations with the Government:`
  line
  line `(12) “Sub-lambardar” means a person so appointed to represent the inferior proprietary body of a`
  line `mahal in its relations with the superior proprietors:`
  line
  line `(13) “Mukaddam” means the executive headman of a village, appointed in manner prescribed by`
  line `this Act:`
  line
  line `(14) “Tenant” means a person who holds land of another person, and is, or but for a special contract`
  line `would be, liable to pay rent for such land to such other person; but it does not include a farmer,`
  line `mortgagee or the kadar of proprietary rights.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—An inferior proprietor is not, as such, a tenant:`
  line
  line `(15) “Rent” means whatever is paid, delivered or rendered, in money, kind or service, by a`
  line `tenant on account of the use or occupation of land let to him:`
  line
  line `(16) “Absolute occupancy-tenant” means, in reference to any land, a tenant who, at a settlement`
  line `of such land made before this Act comes into force, or after such a settlement but before this Act`
  line `comes into force, was recorded, by order of a Revenue or Settlement-officer, in respect of such`
  line `land, as an “absolute occupancy-raiyat,” or in terms equivalent thereto:`
  line
  line `(17) “Record-of-rights” includes the supplementary administration-paper prepared at or after`
  line `the time of making a settlement before this Act comes into force.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (69600)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Chief Controlling Revenue-authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69600&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner shall, subject to the control of`
  line `the Governor General in Council, be the Chief Controlling Revenue-authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (69601)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Revenue-officers.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69601&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Besides the Chief Commissioner, there shall be the following classes of`
  line `Revenue-officers (namely):--`
  line
  line `(a) Commissioners, who, subject to the control of the Chief Commissioner, shall be the Chief`
  line `Revenue-authorities within their respective divisions:`
  line
  line `(b) Deputy Commissioners, who, subject to the control of the Commissioner, shall be the chief`
  line `Revenue-authorities within their respective districts:`
  line
  line `(c) Assistant Commissioners, who shall be subordinate to, and under the control of, the Deputy`
  line `Commissioners of the districts to which they are respectively attached:`
  line
  line `(d) Tahsildars, who, subject to the control of the Deputy Commissioner, shall be the Chief`
  line `Executive Revenue-authorities in the tahsils to which they are respectively attached:`
  line
  line `(e) Naib Tahsildars, who shall be subordinate to the Tahsildars of the tahsils to which they are`
  line `respectively attached.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (69602)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Appointment, suspension and removal of Commissioners, Deputy and Assistant Commissioners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69602&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the control of the Governor General in Council, the Chief Commissioner`
  line `shall appoint, and may suspend or remove, Commissioners, Deputy Commissioners and Assistant`
  line Commissioners.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (69603)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Appointment, suspension and removal of Tahsildars and Naib Tahsildars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69603&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The Chief`
  line `Commissioner shall appoint, and may suspend or remove, Tahsildars; and may also make rules for`
  line `regulating the appointment, duties, suspension and removal of Naib Tahsildars.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (69604)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Persons holding office when Act comes into force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69604&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `All Commissioners, Deputy Commissioners,`
  line `Assistant Commissioners, Tahsildars and Naib Tahsildars holding office as such in the territories to which`
  line `this Act extends when this Act comes into force shall be deemed to have been appointed hereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (69605)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power to appoint additional Commissioners, Deputy Commissioners and Tahsildars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69605&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Chief Commissioner may appoint any person to be an additional Tahsildar in any tahsil, or, with the`
  line `sanction of the Governor General in Council, to be an additional Commissioner or additional Deputy`
  line `Commissioner in any division or district, and may suspend or remove any person so appointed, but subject,`
  line `in the case of an additional Commissioner or additional Deputy Commissioner, to the like sanction.`
  line
  line `The Chief Commissioner may invest any additional Commissioner, Deputy Commissioner or Tahsildar`
  line `appointed under this section with all or any of the powers conferred by this Act on a Commissioner, Deputy`
  line `Commissioner or Tahsildar, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (69606)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Chief Commissioner may invest Assistant Commissioner with powers of Deputy Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69606&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may invest any Assistant Commissioner attached to a district`
  line `with all or any of the powers conferred by this Act on Deputy Commissioners.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (69607)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Officers transferred to retain powers with which they were invested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69607&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any Assistant`
  line `Commissioner, Tahsildar or Naib Tahsildar is transferred from one district or tahsil to another, he shall,`
  line `unless the Chief Commissioner otherwise directs, exercise in the district or tahsil to which he is transferred`
  line `all the powers with which he was, under any provision of this Act, invested by the Chief Commissioner in`
  line `the district or tahsil from which he is transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (69608)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Provision for discharge of duties of Deputy Commissioner dying or being disabled.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69608&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `When a`
  line `Deputy Commissioner dies or is disable from performing his duties, such officer as the Chief Commissioner`
  line `may by rule direct shall take executive charge of his district, and shall be deemed to be a Deputy`
  line `Commissioner under this Act, until a successor to the Deputy Commissioner so dying or disabled is`
  line `appointed and such successor takes charge of his office, or until the person so disabled resumes charge of`
  line `his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (69609)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Chief Commissioner may alter limits of district or tahsil.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69609&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may, from`
  line `time to time, by notification in the official Gazette, alter the limits of any district or tahsil, create new`
  line `districts or tahsils and abolish existing districts or tahsils.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (69770)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power to invest Revenue-officers, — with power conferred by Code of Civil Procedure; with power to delegate powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69770&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may, subject to the control of the`
  line `Governor General in Council, invest any Revenue-officer with any of the following powers:--`
  line
  line `With power conferred by Code of Civil Procedure; for the purpose of disposing of cases under this`
  line `Act, any power conferred by the Code of Civil Procedure on a Civil Court;`
  line
  line `with power to delegate power, ower to delegate to any Revenue-officer subordinate to him the`
  line `exercise of any power of performance of any duty conferred or imposed on him by this Act;`
  line
  line `and, subject to the like control, may determine the Revenue-officer by whom any case or class of`
  line `cases for which no express provision in this behalf is made in this Act shall be disposed of.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (69611)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power of Deputy Commissioners to distribute work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69611&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any rules which the Chief`
  line `Commissioner may make in this behalf, a Deputy Commissioner may--`
  line
  line `(a) refer any case to any Revenue-officer subordinate to him for investigation and report, or, if such`
  line `officer has power to dispose of such case, for disposal; or`
  line
  line `(b) direct that any Revenue-officer subordinate to him shall, without such reference, deal with any`
  line `case or class of cases arising within any specified area, and either investigate and report on such case`
  line `or class, or, if he has power, dispose of it himself.`
  line
  line `The subordinate Revenue-officer shall submit his report on any case referred to him under this`
  line `section for report to the Deputy Commissioner, or otherwise, as may be directed in the order of`
  line `reference; and the officer receiving such report may, if he has power to dispose of the case, dispose of`
  line `the same, or may return it for further investigation to the officer submitting the report, or may hold such`
  line `investigation himself.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (69612)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power of superior Revenue-authorities to withdraw and transfer cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69612&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The Chief`
  line `Commissioner, the Commissioner or the Deputy Commissioner may withdraw any case pending before any`
  line `Revenue-officer subordinate to him, and either dispose of it himself, or refer it for disposal to any other`
  line `Revenue-officer subordinate to him and having power to dispose of the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (69614)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power of Revenue-officers to enter on land, &c.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69614&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `All Revenue-officers and persons acting under`
  line `their orders may, in the performance of any duty under this Act, enter upon and survey land, and demarcate`
  line `boundaries, and do all other acts necessary to the business in which they are engaged.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (69615)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to make rules to regulate procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69615&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may, with the previous`
  line `sanction of the Governor General in Council, make rules consistent with this Act for regulating the`
  line `procedure of Revenue-officers in cases for which a procedure is not prescribed by this Act, and may, by`
  line `any such rule, direct that any provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure shall apply, with or without`
  line `modification, to all or any classes of cases before Revenue-officers.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (69616)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Persons by whom appearances and applications may be made before and to Revenue-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69616&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `All appearances before, applications to, and acts to be done before, any Revenue-officer under`
  line `this Act may be made or done--`
  line
  line `(a) by the parties themselves; or,`
  line
  line `(b) with the permission of the officer, by their recognized agents or any legal practitioner:`
  line
  line `Obligation of parties to attend in person. Provided that the employment of a legal practitioner of`
  line `recognized agent shall not excuse the personal attendance of a party to any proceeding in cases where such`
  line `attendance is required by any order of the Revenue-officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (69617)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Legal practitioner's or agent's fees not allowed unless for special reasons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69617&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The fees of a legal`
  line `practitioner or recognized agent shall not be allowed as costs before any Revenue-officer unless such officer`
  line `considers, for reasons to be recorded by him in writing, that such fees should allowed.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (69618)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69618&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `An appeal shall lie against every decision or order under this Act.`
  line
  line `(a) when such decision or order is passed by any Revenue-officer subordinate to the Deputy`
  line `Commissioner, except an Assistant Commissioner exercising the powers of a Deputy Commissioner,--`
  line `to the Deputy Commissioner;`
  line
  line `(b) when such decision or order is passed by a Deputy Commissioner, or by an Assistant`
  line `Commissioner exercising the powers of a Deputy Commissioner, whether in the first instance or on`
  line `appeal,---to the Commissioner of the division;`
  line
  line `(c) when such decision or order is passed on appeal of otherwise by the Commissioner of a`
  line `division,---to the Chief Commissioner:`
  line
  line `Provided that in no case shall a third appeal be allowed.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (69619)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Limitation of appeals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69619&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `No appeal shall lie--`
  line
  line `(a) in the Court of the Deputy Commissioner or an Assistant Commissioner exercising the powers`
  line `of a Deputy Commissioner---after the expiration of thirty days from the date of the decision or order`
  line `complained of; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the Court of the Commissioner---after the expiration of sixty days from such date; or`
  line
  line `(c) in the Court of the Chief Commissioner---after the expiration of ninety days from such date.`
  line
  line `In computing such periods of limitation, and in all respects not herein specified, the provisions of`
  line `the Indian Limitation Act, 1877, shall apply.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (69620)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Powers of revision of Commissioner and Deputy Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69620&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Any Commissioner or`
  line `Deputy Commissioner may at any time, for the purpose of satisfying himself as to the legality or propriety`
  line `of any order passed by, and as to the regularity of the proceedings of, any Revenue-officer subordinate to`
  line `him, call for and examine the record of any case pending before, or disposed of by, such officer, and may`
  line `pass such order in reference thereto as he thinks fit :`
  line
  line `Provided that he shall not under this section modify or reverse any order affecting any question of right`
  line `between private persons, without having given to the parties interested reasonable notice to appear and be`
  line `heard in support of such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (69621)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Powers of revision or Chief Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69621&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may at any time call for`
  line `and examine the record of any case pending before, or disposed of by, any Revenue-officer, and may pass`
  line `such order in reference thereto as he thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order affecting any question of right between private persons shall be passed under`
  line `this section unless the Chief Commissioner has given the parties interested an opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (69622)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Review of orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69622&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Every Revenue-officer may, either on his own Motion or on the application`
  line `of any party interested, review, and on so reviewing modify, reverse or confirm, orders passed by himself`
  line `or by any of his predecessors in office:`
  line
  line `Provided as follows--`
  line
  line `(1) when a Commissioner or Deputy Commissioner thinks it necessary to review any order which`
  line `he has not himself passed, and when an officer under the rank of a Deputy Commissioner proposes to`
  line `review any order, whether passed by himself or by any predecessor, he shall first obtain the sanction of`
  line `the officer to whom he is immediately subordinate:`
  line
  line `(2) no order shall be modified or reversed unless reasonable notice has been given to the parties`
  line `interested to appear and be heard in support of such order:`
  line
  line `(3) no order against which an appeal has been preferred shall be reviewed while such appeal is`
  line `pending:`
  line
  line `(4) no order affecting any question of right between private persons shall be reviewed except on`
  line `the application of a party to the proceedings; and no application for the review of such an order shall`
  line `be entertained unless it is made within ninety days from the passing of the order, or unless the applicant`
  line `satisfied the Revenue-officer that he had sufficient cause for not making the application within such`
  line period.
  line
  line `For the purposes of this section, the Deputy Commissioner shall be deemed to be the successor in`
  line `office of any Revenue-officer who has left the district or has ceased to exercise powers as a Revenueofficer, and to whom there is no successor in office.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (69624)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Notification of revenue-survey.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69624&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Whenever it appears to the Chief Commissioner`
  line `that a revenue-survey should be made in any local area, he shall publish a notification in the official Gazette`
  line `directing that such survey be made, and cause translations of such notification in the language of the district`
  line `to be posted up in conspicuous places in such area; and thereupon all officers in charge of such survey, their`
  line `assistants, servants, agents and workmen may enter upon the lands to be surveyed, and erect survey-marks,`
  line `and do all other acts necessary for making the survey.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (69625)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Notification of settlement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69625&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `When any local area is to be settled, the Chief Commissioner may,`
  line `with the previous sanction of the Governor General in Council, issue a notification of settlement, and in`
  line `such notification shall---`
  line
  line `(a) define the local area to be settled;`
  line
  line `(b) specify the operations which are to be carried out in the settlement;`
  line
  line `Power to amend notification. and may from time to time, with the like sanction, amend, alter or cancel`
  line `such notification.`
  line
  line `Every such notification, amendment, alteration and cancellation shall be published in the local official`
  line Gazette.
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (69775)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to appoint Settlement-officers; and to suspend and remove them`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69775&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may from time to time appoint`
  line `one or more officers (hereinafter called Settlement-officers) to make the settlement of such area; and when`
  line `he appoints more than one such officer, he shall appoint one of them (hereinafter called the Chief`
  line `Settlement-officer) to control such settlement, an all other officers appointed for the purposes of such`
  line `settlement shall be subordinate to the Chief Settlement officer.`
  line
  line `and to suspend and remove them. The Chief Commissioner may suspend or remove any officer`
  line `appointed under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (69627)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Settlement-officer may be invested with powers of Deputy Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69627&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `During the progress`
  line `of the settlement of any local area, the Chief Commissioner may invest any Settlement-officer within such`
  line `area with all or any of the powers of a Deputy Commissioner under this Act, to be exercised by him in such`
  line `classes of cases as the Chief Commissioner may from time to time direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (69628)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Certain provisions of Chapter II applied to Settlement-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69628&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of section`
  line `eleven and sections fifteen to twenty-six, both inclusive, shall apply, mutatis mutandis, to Settlementofficers and to proceedings before them, the expression "Settlement-officer" being read for the expressions`
  line `"Assistant Commissioner” and "Revenue-officer," and the expression "Chief Settlement-officer" for the`
  line `expression "Deputy Commissioner," wherever those expressions occur:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal from any appealable order passed by a subordinate Settlement-officer shall lie`
  line `to the Chief Settlement-officer if preferred within sixty days from the date of such order:`
  line
  line `Provided also that no appeal shall lie from any decision of a Chief Settlement officer which can be`
  line `called in question in a Civil Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (69777)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Appointment of Settlement-commissioner; delegation to him of Chief Commissioner’s powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69777&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may, from time to time,`
  line `with the previous sanction of the Governor, General in Council,`
  line
  line `(a) appoint a Settlement-commissioner, and transfer to him, within any local area under settlement,`
  line `all or any of the powers which the Commissioner of the division, if the land to be settled were wholly`
  line `situate within such division, would otherwise exercise under this Act in matters connected with such`
  line `settlement; and`
  line
  line `(b) delegation to him of Chief Commissioner's powers. delegate to the Settlement-commissioner`
  line `such of his own powers in regard to matters connected with such settlement as he thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (69630)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Power to invest Settlement-officers with Civil Court powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69630&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `When any local area is under`
  line `settlement, the Chief Commissioner may invest any subordinate Settlement-officer with the powers of any`
  line `of the first five grades of Courts described in section four of the Central Provinces Courts, Act, 1865, and`
  line `the Chief Settlement-officer with the powers of a Court of a Deputy Commissioner described in the same`
  line `Act, sections twelve, nineteen and twenty, for the trial, in the first instance, of any of the following classes`
  line `of suits instituted within such area (namely):--`
  line
  line `(a) suits for arrears of rent due on account of any fight of pasturage, forest-rights, fisheries or the`
  line like;
  line
  line `(b) suits by lambardars for arrears of revenue payable through them by the proprietors whom they`
  line represent;
  line
  line `(c) suits by proprietors for their share of the profits of an estate or any part thereof after payment`
  line `of the revenue and village-expenses, or for a settlement of accounts;`
  line
  line `(d) suits by muafidars or assignees of revenue for arrears of revenue owing to them as such`
  line `muafidars or assignees;`
  line
  line `(e) suits by superior proprietors for arrears of revenue due to them as such superior proprietors;`
  line
  line `(f) suits by proprietors and others in receipt of the rent of land against any agents employed by them`
  line `in the management of land or collection of rents, or against the sureties of such agents, for money`
  line `received or accounts kept by such agents in the course of such employment, or for papers in their`
  line possession;
  line
  line `(g) suits regarding any matter which a Settlement-officer is required to decide or to enter in the`
  line `record-of-rights, and of which Civil Courts can take cognizance;`
  line
  line `(h) suits relating to land, or the rent, profits or occupation of land.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (69631)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Chief Settlement-officer to have powers of Deputy Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69631&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `When the Chief`
  line `Commissioner invests any subordinate Settlement-officer with the powers of a Civil Court for the trial of`
  line `any of the suits mentioned in section thirty-three, the Chief Settlement-officer to whom such Settlementofficer is subordinate shall have the powers of the Court of a Deputy Commissioner described in the Central`
  line `Provinces Courts’ Act, 1865, sections twelve, nineteen and twenty, with reference to proceedings before,`
  line `or decrees and order of, such settlement-officer in such suits.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (69632)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Appeals in suits specified in section 33 when to lie to Chief Settlement-officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69632&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `When any`
  line `local area is under settlement and Settlement-officers have been invested with the powers mentioned in`
  line `section thirty-three in such local area, the Chief Commissioner may, with respect to all or to any of the suits`
  line `specified in that section, declare that all or any of the decrees and orders passed in exercise of the powers`
  line `of Courts of the first four grades aforesaid, by Assistant Commissioners or Tahsildars not being Settlementofficers, shall be appealable to the Chief Settlement-officer, and not to the Deputy Commissioner of the`
  line district.
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (69633)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Division of civil work between Settlement-officers and ordinary Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69633&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `When any local area`
  line `is under settlement and the Settlement-officers therein have been invested with powers under section thirtythree, the Chief Commissioner may withdraw from the jurisdiction of the ordinary Civil Courts within such`
  line `area the classes of suits which Settlement-officers have power to dispose of under that section, or he may`
  line `direct that, in respect of such suits, the Settlement-officers shall have concurrent jurisdiction with the`
  line `ordinary Civil Courts:`
  line
  line `Provided that no proceedings which have been inadvertently or erroneously taken before the Civil Court`
  line `shall be deemed to be invalid merely on the ground that, by the Chief Commissioner's order, they should`
  line `have been taken before a Settlement-officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (69634)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Provisions of section 31 not to apply to certain suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69634&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in section thirty-one shall apply`
  line `to suits and appeals or other proceedings instituted before, or determined by, Settlement-officers in`
  line `pursuance of powers conferred upon them under section thirty-three, thirty-four or thirty-five.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (69635)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Appeal, reference and revision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69635&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `Except as provided in sections thirty-three, thirty-four and`
  line `thirty-five, the decrees and orders of a Settlement-officer passed, whether in the first instance or on appeal,`
  line `in exercise of the powers of a Civil Court of any grade, shall, for the purposes of appeal, reference and`
  line `revision, be deemed to be decrees and orders of a Civil Court of such grade, and no appeal shall lie under`
  line `the provisions of section twenty-two from such decrees or orders.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (69637)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Duration of settlement-operations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69637&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Every settlement notified under section twenty-eight shall`
  line `be deemed to be in progress until the Chief Commissioner, by notification in the official Gazette,`
  line `declares that it is completed.`
  line
  line `Cases pending at close of settlement-operations.--When the settlement of any local area has been notified as completed, all the powers exercised by the Settlement-officers in such area shall cease,`
  line `and all suits and applications pending before such officers shall be transferred to such of the Courts`
  line `ordinarily having jurisdiction in such cases as the Commissioner of the division directs; or, if there are`
  line `no such Courts, shall be disposed of in such manner as the Chief Commissioner directs.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (69638)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Settlement-officer to invite claims to lands appearing to have no owner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69638&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `When any local`
  line `area is under settlement, the Settlement-officer shall make lists of all lands in such area which appear`
  line `to him to have no lawful owner, and shall thereupon issue a notification declaring his intention to`
  line `demarcate such lands as the property of the Government and inviting every person having claims to or`
  line `over them to present in his court, within three months from the date of the notification, a petition in`
  line `writing setting forth such claims and the respective grounds thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (69639)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Application of Act XXIII of 1863.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69639&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `Every such notification shall be deemed to be an`
  line `advertisement under Act No. XXIII of 1863 (to provide for the adjudication of claims to waste lands),`
  line `section one;`
  line
  line `the demarcation of such lands shall be deemed to be a disposition of them within the meaning of`
  line `that Act;`
  line
  line `the Settlement-officer shall exercise all the powers vested in the Collector by that Act; and`
  line
  line `claims to or over the land comprised in such notification shall be dealt with as nearly as may be in`
  line `the manner prescribed in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (69640)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Procedure when limited right over land established.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69640&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Whenever a claim to the exercise or`
  line `enjoyment of any right (not amounting to the right of exclusive possession) in, to or over, any land`
  line `comprised in such notification is established, either before the Settlement-officer or before the Court`
  line `constituted under the said Act No. XXIII of 1863, section seven, the Settlement-officer may assign to`
  line `the claimant as his property a definite portion of such land, or, with the sanction of the Chief`
  line `Commissioner, he may otherwise compensate the claimant; and such assignment or compensation shall`
  line `be held to extinguish all claims on account of such exercise or enjoyment.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (69641)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power to form mahals.`
  content `The Settlement-officer may declare any local area to be a mahal.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69641&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (69642)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Settlement-officer may exclude any town or land from settlement-operations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69642&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `For the`
  line `purpose of excluding from all or any of the operations of the settlement any town or any land from`
  line `which the owner can derive no profit, the Settlement-officer may mark off the site and determine the`
  line `limits of such town or land:`
  line
  line `Provided that no land in respect of which land-revenue payable at the date of the notification issued`
  line `under section twenty-eight shall, under this section, be exempted from assessment without the sanction`
  line `of the Chief Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (69643)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Erection of new, and repair of existing, boundary-marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69643&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `When any local area is under`
  line `settlement, the Settlement-officer may order all persons who have proprietary rights in the land`
  line `comprised in such area to erect boundary-marks of such description and at such places as he thinks`
  line `necessary in order to define the limits of the mahals, fields or other lands in their possession, or to`
  line `repair boundary-marks already existing; and may fix a reasonable time for obeying his order;`
  line
  line `and if his order is not obeyed within such time, may cause such marks to be erected or repaired`
  line `under his own orders, and may recover the cost of such erection or repair from the persons against`
  line `whom his order was made, in such proportion as he thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (69644)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Separate sum to be assessed on every mahal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69644&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `On every mahal a`
  line `definite and separate sum shall be assessed as land-revenue; but the sum so assessed may be reduced`
  line `in such manner and to such extent as the Chief Commissioner thinks fit, for any period not exceeding`
  line `ten years from the date on which the assessment takes effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (69645)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Matters as to which Chief Commissioner is to instruct Settlement-officer`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69645&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `The Chief`
  line `Commissioner may from time to time, with the previous sanction of the Governor General in Council,`
  line `give instructions to the Settlement-officer as to the principle on which land-revenue is to be assessed,`
  line `and as to the sources of miscellaneous income to be taken into account in the assessment.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (69646)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `What land taken into account in assessing mahal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69646&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `In assessing a mahal all land situate therein`
  line `shall be taken into account except the following (that is to say):--`
  line
  line `(a) land purchased free from revenue under any rules for the time being in force to regulate the sale`
  line `of waste-lands;`
  line
  line `(b) land in respect of which the revenue has been redeemed under any rules for the time being in`
  line force;
  line
  line `(c) land excluded from assessment under section forty-four;`
  line
  line `(d) land in respect of which a claim to hold it free from revenue as against the Government is`
  line `established under the provisions hereinafter contained;`
  line
  line `(e) land which the Chief Commissioner, subject to the control of the Governor General in Council,`
  line `may from time to time exempt from assessment.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (69647)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Assessment to whom to be offered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69647&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The assessment of every mahal shall be offered to the`
  line `entire proprietary body of such mahal: provided that, when superior and inferior proprietary rights`
  line `co-exist in the same mahal, the Settlement-officer may, subject to such rules as the Chief Commissioner`
  line `may make in this behalf, determine whether the assessment shall be offered to the superior or to the`
  line `inferior proprietors.`
  line
  line `Subject to such rules as the Chief Commissioner may make in this behalf, the Settlement-officer`
  line `may determine the manner and proportion in which the proprietary profits of the maha1 shall be allotted`
  line `between the superior and the inferior proprietors.`
  line
  line `When a proprietor has mortgaged his rights in any mahal, and the mortgagee has entered into`
  line `possession, such mortgagee, so long as he is in possession, shall, for the purposes of this section, stand`
  line `in the place of the mortgagor.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (69648)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Sub-settlement to be made with inferior proprietors when settlement is made with superior.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69648&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `When in a mahal in which superior and inferior proprietors co-exist, the Settlement-officer makes a`
  line `settlement with the superior proprietors, he shall make on their behalf a sub-settlement with the`
  line `inferior proprietors, by which such inferior proprietors shall be bound to pay to the superior proprietors`
  line `an annual revenue equal to the land-revenue with which the mahal is assessed and to the profits to`
  line `which the superior proprietors are entitled under section forty-nine.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (69649)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Power to give directions as to payment of certain profits of superior proprietors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69649&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `When in`
  line `any such mahal the settlement is made with the inferior proprietors, the Settlement-officer may direct that`
  line `the profits to which the superior proprietors are entitled under section forty-nine, shall be paid by the inferior`
  line `proprietors direct to such superior proprietors, or that such profits shall be collected as if they were landrevenue and shall be paid to the superior proprietors from the Government Treasury.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (69650)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Power to make rules for reporting assessment for sanction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69650&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may`
  line `make rules prescribing the manner in which the Settlement-officer shall report for sanction his rates and`
  line `method of assessment; and no assessment shall be offered without the previous sanction of the Chief`
  line Commissioner.
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (69651)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Offers of assessment to be made subject to revision and confirmation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69651&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `In making any offer of`
  line `assessment the Settlement-officer shall state that it is made subject to confirmation by the Governor General`
  line `in Council, and also to revision by the Chief Commissioner at any time before such confirmation is received.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (69652)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Option to accept or refuse assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69652&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `It shall be in the option of the persons to whom an`
  line `assessment is offered to accept or refuse the same.`
  line
  line `Mode of acceptance. If they are willing to accept it, they shall make and sign an acceptance in writing,`
  line `in such form as the Chief Commissioner may from time to time prescribe in this behalf, and deliver the`
  line `same to the Settlement-officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (69653)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Proprietor not accepting in manner prescribed may be deemed to have accepted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69653&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `proprietor who, within such reasonable period as may be specified by the Chief Commissioner, fails to`
  line `make, sign and deliver such acceptance, or to inform the Settlement-officer that he refuses the proposed`
  line `assessment, shall, if the Settlement-officer by an order in writing so directs, be deemed to have accepted`
  line `such assessment.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (69654)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Effect of acceptance of assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69654&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the assessment of a mahal has been accepted`
  line `under this Act, the persons who have accepted it shall be bound to pay the amount thereof from such date`
  line `and for such term as the Chief Commissioner may appoint in this behalf, or, if at the expiry of that term no`
  line `new assessment has been made and is ready to take effect, until a new assessment has been made and is`
  line `ready to take effect: Provided as follows: --`
  line
  line `Assessmemt may be rescinded by Chief Commissioner; or by Governor General in Council.`
  line
  line `1st---any assessment may be rescinded by the Chief Commissioner at any time before it has been`
  line `confirmed by the Governor General in Council;`
  line
  line `2ndly---the Governor General in Council may rescind any assessment submitted to him for`
  line confirmation;
  line
  line `Malguzrs may object to continuance of assessment beyond term of settlement.`
  line
  line `3rdly--if all the malguzars of a mahal, six months before the expiry of the term fixed under this section,`
  line `apply in writing to the Deputy Commissioner stating that they are unwilling that the assessment should`
  line `continue in force beyond the expiry of such term, the assessment shall, on the expiry of such term, cease to`
  line `be in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (69656)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Procedure when assessment is refused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69656&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `Where there is but one class of proprietors in a mahal,`
  line `and all refuse to accept in manner required by section fifty-four the assessment offered, the Settlementofficer may, with the previous sanction of the Chief Commissioner, exclude them from settlement for a`
  line `period not exceeding thirty years from the date of such exclusion, and may either let the mahal in farm, or`
  line `take it under direct management.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (69657)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Procedure when only some proprietors accept assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69657&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `If some of the proprietors consent,`
  line `and some refuse, so to accept the assessment offered, the Settlement-officer may, with the previous sanction`
  line `of the Chief Commissioner, if the interest of the recusant proprietors in the lands taken into account in the`
  line `assessment consists entirely of lands held by them separately form the other proprietors, exclude such in`
  line `the lands taken into account in the assessment consists entirely of lands held by them separately from the`
  line `other proprietors, exclude such recusant proprietors from settlement for a period not exceeding thirty years`
  line `from the date of such exclusion, and either let their lands in farm or take such lands under direct`
  line management.
  line
  line `In other cases the assessment of the entire mahal shall be offered to the proprietors who consented to`
  line `accept the assessment when originally offered, and if they refuse it the mahal shall be dealt with under the`
  line `provisions of section fifty-seven.`
  line
  line `When the recusant proprietors are excluded under this section, the lands of the proprietors who`
  line `consented to accept the assessment originally offered shall be deemed to be a separate mahal, and shall be`
  line `assessed as such; and such assessment shall be offered to the proprietors so consenting; and if the lands of`
  line `the recusant proprietors are let in farm, the farm shall be first offered to the proprietors who consented to`
  line `accept the assessment originally offered.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (69658)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Procedure on refusal of assessment in village in which superior and inferior rights co-exist.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69658&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `When an assessment is offered in a mahal in which both superior and inferior proprietors co-exist---a) if`
  line `all the proprietors of the class with which the Settlement-officer proposes to make the settlement refuse to`
  line `accept as aforesaid the assessment offered, the assessment shall be offered to the proprietors of the other`
  line `class; and if all such proprietors refuse the assessment, the Settlement-officer shall proceed as provided in`
  line `section fifty-seven;`
  line
  line `(b) if some only of the proprietors of the class with which the Settlement-officer proposes to make the`
  line `settlement refuse the assessment, he may either proceed as if all had refused it or may deal with the mahal`
  line `under section fifty-eight:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, in the case contemplated by clause (b), the proprietors who consented to accept the`
  line `assessment when originally offered refuse to accept it, such assessment shall be offered to the other class`
  line `of proprietors.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (69659)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Procedure on refusal of assessment by inferior proprietors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69659&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `If all or any of the inferior`
  line `proprietors refuse any assessment offered under section fifty, the Settlement-officer may exclude them all`
  line `from the sub-settlement, and assign the proprietary management and profits of the mahal to the superior`
  line `proprietor for any term not exceeding the term of settlement.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (69660)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Allowance to excluded proprietors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69660&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Any proprietor excluded from settlement under section`
  line `fifty-seven or section fifty-nine, clause (a), shall be entitled to receive from the Government an annual`
  line `allowance, the amount of which shall be fixed by the Chief Commissioner but which shall not be less than`
  line `five per cent., or more than ten per cent., on the amount of the assessment offered to him by the Settlement-officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (69661)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Excluded proprietors to have occupancy-rights in their sir-land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69661&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `Any proprietor excluded`
  line `from settlement or sub-settlement under sections fifty-seven to sixty, both inclusive, shall be entitled to`
  line `retain possession of his sir-land (if any) as if he were an absolute occupancy-tenant, and the rent to be paid`
  line `by him for such land during the term of his exclusion shall be fixed by the Settlement-officer accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (69778)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Aggregate amount of allowance granted to, and deduction from rent allowed to, excluded proprietor`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69778&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `The aggregate amount of any allowance under section sixty-one, and of the difference`
  line `between the rent fixed under section sixty-two and the rent which the excluded proprietor would be liable`
  line `to pay if he were a tenant-at-will, shal1 not be less than five or more than fifteen per cent. on the amount of`
  line `the assessment offered to him by the Settlement-officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (69663)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Sub-settlement with malik-makbuzas and other like holders of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69663&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `The Settlement-officer`
  line `may make, on behalf of malik-makbuzas or other like holders of land, such a sub-settlement as shall secure`
  line `to them from the malguzars of the mahal their existing rights; and may provide that, in addition to the landrevenue payable by them, they shall pay to the malguzars such percentage thereon, not exceeding twenty`
  line `per cent., as may in his opinion be sufficient to compensate the said malguzars for their responsibility in`
  line `respect of the land-revenue, and to provide for the fees of lambardars and mukaddams.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (69664)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Revenue payable under sub-settlement to be first charge on land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69664&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `The amount of revenue`
  line `payable under a sub-settlement shall be a first charge upon all the land comprised in such sub-settlement.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (69665)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Settlement-officer to apportion assessment over lands held in severalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69665&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `When the whole of`
  line `the land comprised in a mahal is held in severalty, the Settlement-officer shall apportion to the several`
  line `holdings the amount with which such land is assessed under a settlement or sub-settlement.`
  line
  line `When only part of the land comprised in a mahal is held in severalty, the Settlement-officer shall`
  line `apportion such amount to the part held in common and the part held in severalty, and shall further apportion`
  line `to the several holdings the amount to which they are liable under the former apportionment.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (69666)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `to redistribute land according to custom.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69666&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `When by established custom the land held by each`
  line `proprietor in any mahal is subject to periodical redistribution, the Settlement-officer may, in his discretion,`
  line `on the application of the proprietors, make such redistribution according to such custom.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (69667)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Settlement-officer to ascertain proprietors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69667&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `The Settlement-officer shall ascertain the persons`
  line `who are in possession as proprietors of the land comprised in each mahal.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (69668)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `to determine extent of sir-land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69668&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `The Settlement-officer shall ascertain the situation and`
  line `determine the extent of all the land held as sir in each malal.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (69669)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `to decide disputes among shareholders regarding management of mahal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69669&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `The Settlementofficer shall ascertain the customs or rules by which the proprietors in each mahal are mutually bound as to`
  line `the granting of pattas the ejectment of tenants, the realization and distribution of rents and other profits, the`
  line `payment of land revenue, village-expenses and other charges, and generally as to the control and`
  line `management of the mahal; and shall decide all disputes and record all agreements regarding the matters`
  line `mentioned in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (69670)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `to determine through what lambardars revenue shall be paid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69670&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `The Settlement-officer shall`
  line `determine through which of the lambardars or sub-lambardars the amount of revenue payable by each`
  line `proprietor, sub-proprietor or malik-makbuza shall be paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (69671)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `to ascertain status and rents of tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69671&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `The Settlement-officer shall ascertain, and record for`
  line `each mahal, the status of all tenants occupying land therein, the lands respectively held by them, the`
  line `conditions on which they respectively hold such lands, and the rents (if any) payable by them respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (69672)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Enquiry into claims to hold free from revenue as against Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69672&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `The Settlement-officer`
  line `shall investigate all claims against the Government to hold land free from revenue or at less than a full`
  line `assessment, or to receive the whole or part of the land-revenue assessed on land which is not free from`
  line revenue.
  line
  line `Power of Chief Commissioner to make rules.---The Chief Commissioner may, with the previous`
  line `sanction of the Governor General in Council, make rules determining the principles by which the`
  line `Settle-ment-officer shall be guided in the disposal of claims coming under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (69673)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Enquiry as to claims to hold free from revenue as against malguzars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69673&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `When any land not`
  line `being land which any person is entitled to hold free from revenue as against the Government is held by a`
  line `proprietor, whether himself a malguzar or not, who claims to hold it wholly or partially free from revenue`
  line `as against the other malguzars of the mahal, the Settlement-officer shall decide whether the claimant is`
  line `entitled to be exempted from paying the whole or any part of the revenue which would otherwise be payable`
  line `in respect of such land, and, if he decides that the claimant is so entitled, shall also determine the conditions`
  line `under which, and the term for which, the claimant is entitled to such exemption:`
  line
  line `Provided that no decision under this section shall exempt any land from the payment of revenue, when`
  line `the mahal in which such land is comprised is sold for arrears of revenue.`
  line
  line `Chief Commissioner may make rules for disposal of such cases.--The Chief Commissioner may`
  line `make rules for the guidance of Settlement-officers in dealing with cases under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (69674)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Time from which orders under sections 73 and 74 take effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69674&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `When the Settlement-officer`
  line `decides, under section seventy-three or section seventy-four, that land which has been held free from`
  line `revenue, or at less than a full assessment, is liable to pay revenue, or to pay the same at enhanced rates,`
  line `such decision shall take effect from the first day of the agricultural year next ensuing; unless the Chief`
  line `Commissioner directs that the amount payable in respect of such land on account of the revenue accruing`
  line `due within anyone or more of the last preceding twelve years shall be realized.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (69675)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Settlement-officer to decide what village-cesses are leviable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69675&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `The Settlement-officer shall`
  line `determine and record the village-cesses if any which are leviable in accordance with village-custom, and`
  line `the persons by and from whom, and the rates at which, they are leviable; and such cesses shall, if sanctioned`
  line `by the Chief Commissioner, be leviable accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (69676)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `to determine certain disputes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69676&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `The Settlement-officer may determine disputes regarding any of`
  line `the following matters (namely):--`
  line
  line `(a) the right of any lambardar, mukaddam, patwari, village-watchman or other village-servant to`
  line `any customary dues, or other remuneration, and his liability to render any customary service in return`
  line `for such dues or remuneration;`
  line
  line `(b) the rights of persons resident in the village or holding lands comprised in the mahal, in or to`
  line `the common land of the mahal and its produce, and the village-site;`
  line
  line `(c) any customs relating to irrigation or to rights-of-way and other easements;`
  line
  line `(d) any other rights and customs which the Chief Commissioner directs to be recorded in the`
  line administration-paper.
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (69677)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Procedure in cases under sections 68,69,70,72 and 77, clauses (b), (c) and (d).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69677&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `If a dispute`
  line `arises regarding any matter mentioned or referred to in sections sixty-eight, sixty-nine, seventy,`
  line `seventy-two and seventy-seven, clauses (b), (c) and (d), the Settlement-officer shall decide it summarily`
  line `after making such enquiry as he thinks fit, and shall not be bound to hear any party to such dispute or to`
  line `receive any evidence tendered by any such party; but in the case of every such dispute he shall record a`
  line `proceeding stating the nature of such dispute,· his decision thereon, the grounds of such decision and such`
  line `other particulars as he thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (69678)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title Record-of-rights.
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69678&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `The Settlement-officer shall prepare for every mahal, or, if he thinks fit, for`
  line `any group of neighbouring mahals, a record-of-rights, and shall include in it--`
  line
  line `(a) the results of the inquiries made under this chapter in respect of such mahal or group; and`
  line
  line `(b) any other matters which the Chief Commissioner may, by rules in this behalf, direct to be`
  line `entered in such paper.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (69679)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Chief Commissioner may make rules regarding record-of-rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69679&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner`
  line `may make rules prescribing the language in which the record-of-rights shall be drawn up, the form of the`
  line `papers of which it shall consist, and the manner in which such papers shall be signed and attested by the`
  line `Settlement-officer and the parties interested in the matters to which they refer.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (69680)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Record-of-rights to be made over to Deputy Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69680&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `When the Settlement-officer has`
  line `completed a record-of-rights in manner hereinbefore prescribed, he shall, subject to any order issued by the`
  line `Chief Commissioner in this behalf, make it over to the Deputy Commissioner for custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (69681)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Effect of entries in record-of-rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69681&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `When the record-of-rights is duly made and attested, all`
  line `entries therein shall be presumed to be correct until the contrary is shown.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (69682)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Suits to contest certain settlement decisions or entries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69682&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `Any person deeming himself aggrieved`
  line `by any decision under section seventy-eight, or by any decision of the Chief Settlement-officer in appeal`
  line `therefrom or by any entry made in the record-of-rights as to any matter referred to in that section, may`
  line `institute a suit in the Civil Court to have such decision set aside or such entry cancelled or amended:`
  line
  line `Provided as follows:--`
  line
  line `When any suit under this section is instituted for the cancellation or amendment of an entry, the`
  line `Government, if it so desires, and all persons interested in the entry, shall be made parties to the suit:`
  line
  line `No persons by whom the record-of-rights was signed, and no persons claiming through or under them`
  line `shall, without the previous sanction of the Chief Commissioner, institute any suit with a view to modify or`
  line `set aside any entry relating to any matter mentioned in section seventy or section seventy-seven, clause (b),`
  line `(c) or (d).`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (69684)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Revision of record-of-rights by Chief Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69684&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `After an assessment has been confirmed`
  line `by the Governor General in Council, the Chief Commissioner shall not exercise, in respect of any entry of`
  line `the descriptions referred to in section eighty-three duly made in a record-of-rights prepared in connection`
  line `with such assessment and duly attested, the power of revision conferred by sections twenty-five and thirtyone, unless it is proved that such entry was made inadvertently.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (69685)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Proceedings regarding lands the property of Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69685&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `In respect of lands declared to be`
  line `the property of Government, the Settlement-officer shall, instead of proceeding as hereinbefore provided,`
  line `conduct such operations, and prepare such record, as the Chief Commissioner may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (69686)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Former settlements deemed to have been made under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69686&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `Settlements made before this`
  line `Act comes into force shall be deemed, so far as may be, to have been made hereunder; and the provisions`
  line `of this Act in regard to proceedings taken and records prepared by Settlement offices in the making of`
  line `settlements hereunder shall apply in like manner to proceedings taken and records prepared before this Act`
  line `comes into force.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (69687)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Effect of awards of proprietary rights at such settlements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69687&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `When a Settlement-officer or`
  line `Settlement Court has, at any settlement made before this Act comes into force, made an award of proprietary`
  line `rights in any land, all claims which after consideration by such officer or Court may have been expressly`
  line
  line `decided by him or it to be invalid, or inferior to the claims of the persons in whose favour the award was`
  line `made, shall be barred both as against Government and as against the persons last mentioned; and no suit`
  line `shall lie for the enforcement of such claims in any Civil Court.`
  line
  line `The award at any such settlement of proprietary rights in land to a widow shall be deemed to confer on`
  line `her those rights only which, in accordance with the personal law to which she is subject, she would enjoy`
  line `in land inherited by her from her husband.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (69688)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `When suits for proprietary rights will lie in Civil Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69688&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `Any person whose claim to`
  line `proprietary rights in any land was not expressly decided by such officer or Court may sue in a Civil Court`
  line `to establish such claim; and if he can prove that, when proprietary rights in such land were awarded by such`
  line `officer or Court to other persons, he was entitled to interests therein of the same nature as those upon`
  line `consideration of which the award was made, the Civil Court may declare him entitled to a proprietary right`
  line `of such nature and extent in the land as it may deem just.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (69689)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Chief Commissioner may allot waste-land to malik-mak-buzas entitled thereto.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69689&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `When at any`
  line `settlement made before this Act comes into force malik-makbuzas have been declared entitled to a portion`
  line `of the waste-lands comprised in any mahal the Chief Commissioner may, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the record of such settlement, prescribe the extent of such portion and the mode in which the`
  line `same shall be assigned to them; and may determine the nature and extent of their interests therein and the`
  line `conditions on which they may hold it.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (69690)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Power of Chief Commissioner to regulate payment of land-revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69690&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line Notwithstanding
  line `anything contained in the record-of-rights of any village, the Chief Commissioner may fix the number and`
  line `amount of the instalments, and the times, places and manner, at and in which land-revenue, whether payable`
  line `direct to the Government or not, shall be paid.`
  line
  line `Until the Chief Commissioner otherwise directs, all such payments shall be made on the dates, in the`
  line `instalments, in the manner and at the places on, in and at which they are payable when this Act comes into`
  line force.
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (69781)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title Arrear.Defaulters.
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69781&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `When any sum payable under a settlement or sub-settlement is not paid`
  line `within the time at which it is payable under section ninety, such sum shall be deemed to be an arrear, and`
  line `all the persons with whom such settlement or sub-settlement was made, their representatives and assigns,`
  line `shall thereupon become jointly and severally liable for it, and shall be deemed to be defaulters within the`
  line `meaning of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (69692)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Tahasildar's statement of account to be conclusive evidence of arrear.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69692&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `A statement of account,`
  line `authenticated by the signature of the Tahsildar, shall, for the purposes of this chapter, be conclusive`
  line `evidence of the existence of any arrear payable direct to the Government, of its amount, and of the persons`
  line `who in respect thereof are defaulters.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (69693)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Notice of demand.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69693&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `A statement of account,`
  line `authenticated by the signature of the Tahsildar, shall, for the purposes of this chapter, be conclusive`
  line `evidence of the existence of any arrear payable direct to the Government, of its amount, and of the persons`
  line `who in respect thereof are defaulters.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (69694)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Processes for recovery of arrears.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69694&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `An arrear payable directly to Government may be recovered`
  line `by anyone or more of the following processes:—`
  line
  line `(a) by arresting the defaulter and imprisoning him in the civil jail;`
  line
  line `(b) by attaching and selling his moveable property;`
  line
  line `(c) by attaching the mahal in respect of which the arrear has accrued or the share or land of any`
  line `malguzar who has not paid the portion of the revenue which, as between him and the other malguzars,`
  line `is payable by him, and taking the same mahal, share or land under direct management;`
  line
  line `(d) by transferring the share or land of any malguzar who has not paid such portion to any malguzar`
  line `who has paid the same, or, if every such malguzar declines to accept such share or land, to any person`
  line `having a mortgage or charge upon the same, and who consents to accept it;`
  line
  line `(e) by annulling the settlement of the mahal in respect of which the arrear has accrued, and taking`
  line `such mahal under direct management or farming the same;`
  line
  line `(f) by selling such mahal, or the share or land of any malguzar who has not paid the portion of the`
  line `revenue aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(g) by selling immoveable property belonging to the defaulter other than the land in respect of which`
  line `the arrear has accrued:`
  line
  line `Provided as follows:—`
  line
  line `(1) the process mentioned in clause (a) shall not be issued against any female, minor, lunatic or idiot;`
  line
  line `(2) the processes mentioned in clauses (d), (e), (f) and (g) shall not be enforced without the previous`
  line `sanction of the Chief Commissioner;`
  line
  line `(3) No land shall be sold, and the settlement of no land shall be annulled, on account of an arrear`
  line `accruing in respect of land whilst it is under attachment, or under charge of the Superintendent of`
  line `Government Wards, or held under direct management, or let in farm in accordance with any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line `The processes specified in clauses (a), (b) and (g) may be enforced either in the district in which the`
  line `default has been made, or in any other district.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (69695)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Arrest and imprisonment for recovery of arrear.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69695&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `The process mentioned in section`
  line `ninety-four, clause (a), may be executed by issuing a warrant directing the officer named therein, if the`
  line `defaulter fails to pay the arrear by a date to be fixed in the warrant, to bring him to the tahsil.`
  line
  line `If, when the defaulter arrives at the tahsil, the arrear is still unpaid, the Tahsildar may order him to be`
  line `taken before the Deputy Commissioner, or may keep him under personal restraint at the tahsil for a period`
  line `not exceeding ten days, unless within such period the arrear is paid, and may then, if the arrear is still`
  line `unpaid, cause him to be taken before the Deputy Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (69696)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Imprisonment of defaulter in civil jail.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69696&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `If the arrear is not paid when the defaulter arrives before`
  line `the Deputy Commissioner, the Deputy Commissioner may issue an order to the officer in charge of the civil`
  line `jail of the district, directing him to confine the defaulter in such jail for such period, not exceeding three`
  line `months from the date of the order, as the Deputy Commissioner may think fit, unless within such period`
  line `the arrear is paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (69697)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Procedure in sales of moveable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69697&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `Attachments and sales of moveable property made`
  line `under this chapter shall be conducted as nearly as may be according to the law for the time being in force`
  line `for the attachment and sale of moveable property under the decree of a Civil Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (69698)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Management of mahal, share of land attached under section 94(c).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69698&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `After causing any`
  line `attachment to be made under section ninety-four, clause (c), the Deputy Commissioner shall issue a proclamation declaring the attachment to be in force, and shall take the attached mahal, share or land under`
  line `his own management, or place it under the management of any agent whom he may appoint for the purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (69699)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Effect of attachment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69699&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `During the continuance of an attachment under section ninety-eight, the`
  line `defaulters shall be excluded from possession of the land attached, and the Deputy Commissioner or the`
  line `agent appointed by him shall have all their rights to manage the land and to realize the rents and profits`
  line `arising therefrom, and shall be bound by all their liabilities as malguzars or proprietors to any subordinate`
  line `proprietors or tenants of such land.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (69700)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Profits of land how applied.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69700&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `The surplus profits of such land, after defraying the cost of`
  line `attachment and management, shall be applied, first, to the payment of any revenue becoming due in respect`
  line `of such land during the attachment; and next, to discharging the arrear for the recovery of which the`
  line `attachment was made.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (69701)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Attachment when to cease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69701&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `The attachment shall continue until the arrear is paid or realized`
  line `from the profits of the land attached, or the Deputy Commissioner reinstates the defaulters in possession:`
  line
  line `Provided that no attachment shall continue beyond five years from the first day of the agricultural year`
  line `next following its commencement.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (69702)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Transfer under section 94(d).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69702&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `When it is proposed to execute the process mentioned in section`
  line `ninety-four, clause (d), the persons to whom the share or land in respect of which the arrear is due is to be`
  line `transferred shall be required to pay such arrear, or to secure its payment to the satisfaction of the Deputy`
  line Commissioner.
  line
  line `No such transfer shall be made for a term exceeding fifteen years from the first day of the agricultural`
  line `year next after the date on which it is sanctioned by the Chief Commissioner.`
  line
  line `Joint and several liability not affected by transfer.--No proceedings taken under this section shall`
  line `affect the joint and several liability of the malguzars of the mahal for arrears accruing in respect of such`
  line `mahal subsequently to the transfer of the share or land, except that, as regards all such arrears, the transferee`
  line `shall stand in the place of the malguzar whose share or land is transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (69703)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Procedure after receipt of sanction to annulment of settlement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69703&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `When the Chief`
  line `Commissioner sanctions the annulment of the settlement of any mahal, the Deputy Commissioner shall`
  line `proclaim such annulment, and may then exclude the defaulters from the possession of the mahal, and either`
  line `manage the mahal or any portion thereof himself or through an agent, or let the mahal or any portion thereof`
  line `in farm for such term and on such conditions as the Chief Commissioner directs:`
  line
  line `Provided that no management or farm under this section shall continue for a longer period than fifteen`
  line `years from the first day of the agricultural year next after the proclamation of annulment of settlement.`
  line
  line `After the date of such proclamation no liabilities shall accrue under the settlement so annulled; but such`
  line `annulment shall not affect anything done or any liability incurred under the settlement before such date.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (69704)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Case of a portion of a mahal being managed or farmed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69704&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `When a portion only of the mahal is`
  line `managed or let in farm under section one hundred and three, the rest of such mahal shall be separately`
  line `resettled with the proprietors thereof for the remainder of the term of settlement.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (69705)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Settlement on expiry of management or farm.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69705&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `As soon as the management or farm of any`
  line `mahal or portion thereof has come to an end, the Deputy commissioner shall offer to the persons entitled`
  line `under section forty-nine to an offer of assessment a new assessment of the land, on such conditions as the`
  line `Chief Commissioner may direct, for the remainder of the term of the settlement of the mahel; and, if such`
  line `offer is refused, may, with the previous sanction of the Chief Commissioner, let such mahal or portion in`
  line `farm for the remainder of the term of settlement to some other person, or manage it himself or through an`
  line `agent for such period.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (69707)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Effect of annulment of settlement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69707&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `No leases, liens or other incumbrances created by the`
  line `defaulters, or by any person through or under whom they claim, of, or upon any land managed or let in farm`
  line `under this Act, shall, during such management or farm, be binding upon the Deputy Commissioner or`
  line `Settlement-officer, his agent or lessee.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (69708)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Saving of rights in sir-land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69708&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `No defaulter shall be deprived of the possession of his sir-land in`
  line `the execution of any of the processes mentioned in section ninety-four, clauses (c), (d) and (e); but every`
  line `such defaulter shall, while such process is being enforced, be entitled to retain possession of, and liable to`
  line `pay rent for, such land as if he were an absolute occupancy-tenant, at such rent as may be fixed by the`
  line `Deputy Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (69709)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Nature of estate taken by purchaser of land sold for arrears due thereon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69709&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `Unless the Chief`
  line `Commissioner in sanctioning the sale otherwise directs, a purchaser of any land sold for arrears of revenue`
  line `due in respect their of acquires the full proprietorship or superior or inferior proprietorship of it, as the case`
  line `may be, free of all leases, liens and other incumbrances; and all grants or contracts previously made by any`
  line `person other than the purchaser in respect of such land shall become void as against such purchaser.`
  line `Nothing in this section shall--`
  line
  line `(a) affect the rights of any proprietor, superior or inferior to the defaulters, or of any malik-makbuza`
  line `or occupancy-tenant, who does not derive his rights as such proprietor, malik-makbuza or tenant from`
  line `express contract with such defaulters, or any person through whom they claim; or`
  line
  line `(b) apply to lands held under leases at fair rents for the erection thereon of dwelling-houses, places`
  line `of worship or manufactories, or for working mines, minerals, coals and quarries, or for laying out and`
  line `maintaining gardens and burial-grounds, or for constructing tanks and canals, so long as the lands`
  line `continue to be used for the purposes specified in such leases respectively; or`
  line
  line `(c) deprive any defaulter whose property is sold of the rights in respect to his sir-land conferred by`
  line `any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `The Chief Commissioner may, from time to time, determine what rents shall be deemed to be fair`
  line `rents within the meaning of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (69710)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Rules for sale of immoveable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69710&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `When immoveable property is sold under this Act, the`
  line `rules prescribed in sections 287, 288, 293 and 306 to 316, both inclusive, of the Code of Civil Procedure`
  line `shall be followed, except in the following particulars (that is to say):--`
  line
  line `(a) The defaulter may pay the arrear in respect of which the land is to be sold at any time before`
  line `the day fixed for the sale, and on such payment the sale shall be stayed.`
  line
  line `(b) The proclamation directed by the said section 287 shall, when the sale is under clause (f),section`
  line `ninety-four, of this Act, declare that, subject to the provisions of section one hundred and eight, the full`
  line `proprietorship, or superior or inferior proprietorship, as the case may be, is to be sold free from all`
  line `leases, liens, and other incumbrances, and the certificate mentioned in section 316 of the said Code`
  line `shall contain a similar statement.`
  line
  line `(c) The last two clauses of the said section 287 shall not apply.`
  line
  line `(d) An appeal from any order under section 312 of the said Code for confirming or setting aside the`
  line `sale shall lie to the Commissioner of the Division, and an appeal from the Commissioner's order on`
  line `such appeal shall lie to the Chief Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(e) The Deputy Commissioner may, from time to time postpone any sale which he has proclaimed,`
  line `reporting such postponement to the Commissioner of the Division.`
  line
  line `(f) Section 309 of the said Code shall be read as if, after the words “for such payment,” the words`
  line `"and every sale of such property made after a postponement” were added.`
  line
  line `(g) Section 313 of the said Code shall not apply to sales under section ninety-four, clause (f), of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(h) Section 316 of the said Code shall be read as if the words “The Deputy Commissioner shall`
  line `place the purchaser in possession of the lands which he has purchased” were added thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (69711)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Pre-emption at sales.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69711&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `In the course of a sale under section ninety-four, clause (f), if the property`
  line `is knocked down to a stranger, the following persons may claim to take it at the sum last bid in the following`
  line `order:--`
  line
  line `(a) any malguzar who has paid the revenue which, as between him and the other malguzars, is`
  line `payable by him;`
  line
  line `(b) if the superior proprietorship is sold, the inferior proprietor;`
  line
  line `(c) if the inferior proprietorship is sold, the superior proprietor;`
  line
  line `Provided that such claim is made before the officer conducting the sale closes the sitting at which`
  line `the sale is held, and that the claimant undertakes to fulfil all the conditions of the sale binding on the`
  line purchaser.
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (69712)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title `Application of proceeds of sale of immoveable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69712&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `The proceeds of every sale in`
  line `execution of any process mentioned in section ninety-four shall be applied, first, in satisfaction of the arrear`
  line `on account of which the sale was held and of the expenses of such sale; secondly, to the payment of any`
  line `other arrear due to Government by the defaulter; and the surplus, if any, shall then be payable to him, or,`
  line `where there are more defaulters than one, to such defaulters according to their respective shares in the`
  line `property sold.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (69713)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `Costs recoverable as part of arrear.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69713&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `The costs of serving a notice of demand under section`
  line `ninety-three and of enforcing any process mentioned in section ninety-four shall be recoverable as part of`
  line `the arrear in respect of which the notice was served and the process was issued.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (69714)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 113
  title `Matters as to which Chief Commissioner may make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69714&sectionno=113&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may`
  line `make rules--`
  line
  line `(a) for the guidance of Revenue-officers in issuing notices demand under section ninety-three and`
  line `executing the processes mentioned in section ninety-four;`
  line
  line `(b) defining the classes of officers by whom the processes mentioned in section ninety-four,`
  line `clauses (a) and (b), may be enforced;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribing the agency by which any of the processes issued under section ninety-four shall be`
  line executed.
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (69715)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 114
  title `Remedies open to person denying that sum demanded as an arrear is due.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69715&sectionno=114&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line Notwithstanding
  line `anything contained in section ninety-two, when proceedings are taken under this Act for the recovery of an`
  line `arrear, the person against whom such proceedings are taken may, if he denies that the arrear or any part`
  line `thereof is due pay the same under protest made at the time of payment and duly signed by him or by his`
  line `agent, and institute a suit in the Civil Court for the recovery of the amount which he denies to be due.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (69716)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 115
  title `Limitation of right to set-off, &c., in suit for arrears.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69716&sectionno=115&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `In a suit for the recovery of an arrear of`
  line `revenue not being revenue payable directly to Government, and in a suit brought by a lambardar to recover`
  line `the amount of any revenue payable to Government through him, the defendant shall not, except with the`
  line `permission of the Court,--`
  line
  line `(a) Set-off against the plaintiff's demand any sum of money recoverable by him from the`
  line `plaintiff; or`
  line
  line `(b) claim credit for any payment purporting to have been made on account when such payment was`
  line `made before the date on which the amount thereof became due.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (69717)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 116
  title `Recovery of arrear through Deputy Commissioner instead of by suit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69717&sectionno=116&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `Any lambardar or`
  line `sub-lambardar entitled to recover an arrear, or any malguzar whom sue an arrear is due under a`
  line `sub-settlement, may, before instituting a suit for the recovery thereof, apply to the Deputy Commissioner`
  line `to recover such arrear on his behalf as if it were an arrear of revenue payable directly to Government.`
  line
  line `The Deputy Commissioner may, if he thinks fit, comply with such application, but shall, before`
  line `compliance therewith, give to the persons who would be defendants if a suit were instituted for the recovery`
  line `of such arrear, opportunity to show cause against the order which he proposes to make.`
  line
  line `The Deputy Commissioner shall not be made a defendant to any suit instituted under section`
  line `one hundred and fourteen in respect of an arrear as to which an order has been made under this section.`
  line
  line `No person on whose account the Deputy Commissioner proceeds under this section to recover an arrear`
  line `shall thereby be relieved of his responsibility for such arrear.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (69718)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 117
  title `Saving of right of malguzar to demand revenue of land assessed to revenue and held free.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69718&sectionno=117&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in the Indian Limitation Act, 1877, and no agreement made after this Act comes into force,`
  line `shall bar the right of the malguzars of any mahal assessed with land-revenue to demand revenue, in`
  line `respect of any land which, having been taken into account in such assessment, has been held by`
  line `any, person without payment of revenue.`
  line
  line `The Chief Commissioner may, in his discretion, exempt any case from the operation of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (69719)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 118
  title `Limitation in suits for revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69719&sectionno=118&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `No suit for the recovery of revenue payable under a`
  line `settlement or sub-settlement shall be instituted after three years reckoned from the date on which such`
  line `revenue becomes payable.`
  line
  line `In other respects the limitation of such suits shall be governed by the Indian Limitation`
  line `Act, 1877.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (69720)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 119
  title `Interest on arrears.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69720&sectionno=119&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `Interest shall not be charged on an arear of revenue unless the Chief`
  line `Commissioner, by general or special order, so directs; provided that the Court may award interest at such`
  line `rate as it thinks fit on sums payable under a sub-settlement.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (69721)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 120
  title `Correction of record-of-rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69721&sectionno=120&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `Any entry in the record of rights may, after such record has`
  line `been made over to the Deputy Commissioner, be corrected by the Deputy Commissioner on the application`
  line `of any person interested, or of his own motion. Such correction may be made on one or more of the`
  line `following grounds and on no others:--`
  line
  line `(a) that all persons interested in such entry wish to have it corrected; or`
  line
  line `(b) that by a decree in a suit brought under section eighty-three it has been declared to be erroneous;`
  line
  line `(c) that, being founded on a decree or order of a Civil Court, or on the order of a Revenue or`
  line `Settlement-officer, it is not in accordance with such decree or order; or`
  line
  line `(d) that, being founded on such decree or order, the order or decision has subsequently been`
  line `modified on appeal or review, or has been revised by the Chief Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (69722)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 121
  title `Revision of record in accordance with provision therein contained.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69722&sectionno=121&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `The Deputy`
  line `Commissioner may revise a record-of-rights when such revision is provided for in such record.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (69723)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 122
  title `Powers of Deputy Commissioner as to correction of entry or revision of record.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69723&sectionno=122&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `When the`
  line `Deputy Commissioner takes proceedings for the correction of any entry in the record-of-rights or for the`
  line `revision of such record-of-rights, he shall exercise, for the purpose of such correction or revision, all the`
  line `powers which the Chief Settlement-officer might have exercised if the proceedings had been taken whilst`
  line `the settlement was in progress.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (69724)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 123
  title `Power to direct that rule or custom entered in record-of-rights shall be enforced by Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69724&sectionno=123&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may, in his discretion, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct that any specified rule, custom or condition duly entered in the record-of-rights of any specified`
  line `village shall be enforced by the Government.`
  line
  line `Punishment of violation of such rules or custom.-- If any of the persons with whom a settlement or`
  line `sub-settlement has been made, violate or neglect any rule, custom or condition with respect to which the`
  line `Chief Commissioner has made a direction under this section, the Deputy Commissioner may, if no penalty`
  line `is provided by any law for the time being in force for such violation or neglect, recover from such person`
  line `a penalty not exceeding two hundred rupees`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (69725)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 124
  title `Suit to set aside proceedings under section 123.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69725&sectionno=124&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `Any person against whom proceedings have`
  line `been taken under section one hundred and twenty-three may institute a suit against Government to set aside`
  line `such proceedings on the ground that no rule, custom or condition was, in fact, violated or neglected. If the`
  line `Court finds that no rule, custom or condition has been violated or neglected, it may by its order annul such`
  line `proceedings, and direct that any penalty paid by the plaintiff be refunded; and may also award to him such`
  line `costs as he has necessarily incurred in the proceedings, and such further sum as compensation as it thinks`
  line fit.
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (69726)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 125
  title `Powers of Chief Commissioner as to registration of changes after preparation of record-of-rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69726&sectionno=125&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner`
  line
  line `(a) direct that the mukaddam of each village shall, for the purpose of showing the changes occurring`
  line `therein subsequently to the preparation of the record-of-rights, prepare, or, where there is a patwari,`
  line `cause to be prepared, and furnish, annually for such village, papers in such form at such time, containing`
  line `such particulars, and attested in such manner, as the Chief Commissioner may, from time to time,`
  line prescribe;
  line
  line `(b) lay down the procedure to be followed in order to ascertain that a change has occurred in the`
  line `village, and the nature of such change.`
  line
  line `(b)All changes referred to in this section shall be recorded in such registers as the Chief Commissioner`
  line `appoints, and not in the record-of-rights, and the Chief Commissioner may direct that, before any`
  line `specified changes are recorded, the order of a specified Revenue-officer shall be obtained in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (69727)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 126
  title `Possession of proprietary rights to be notified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69727&sectionno=126&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `All persons lawfully entering into possession`
  line `of proprietary rights and interests in any land shall, within a reasonable time, give notice of such entry to`
  line `the Tahsildar of the tahsil in which such land is situated.`
  line
  line `If any question arises whether any right or interest is a proprietary right or interest within the meaning`
  line `of this section, the decision thereof by the Chief Commissioner shall be final.`
  line
  line `Notice to be given by guardian in case of minority or idiotcy.--If the person so entering is a minor,`
  line `lunatic or idiot, the guardian or other person who has charge of his property shall give the notice require by`
  line `this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (69728)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 127
  title `Fine for neglect to give notice of possession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69728&sectionno=127&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `Any person neglecting to give the notice required`
  line `by section one hundred and twenty-six shall be liable, at the discretion of the Deputy Commissioner or`
  line `Assistant Commissioner, to fine which may extend to fifty rupees for each day during which such neglect`
  line continues.
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (69729)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 128
  title `Obligation to aid in preparation of village-papers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69729&sectionno=128&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `All persons being in possession of`
  line `proprietary rights in land shall, on being so required by the Deputy Commissioner, prepare, or cause to be`
  line `prepared, such papers, and furnish such information, as may be required for the preparation of the villagepapers prescribed under section only hundred and twenty-five.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (69783)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 129
  title `Fees for recording changes; from whom leviable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69783&sectionno=129&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may direct that fees shall be leviable`
  line `when changes are recorded under the last clause of section one hundred and twenty-five, and may fix the`
  line `amount of such fees.`
  line
  line `from whom leviable.--All fees so leviable shall be levied from the person in whose favour the change`
  line `is made.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (69733)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 131
  title `Inspection of revenue-records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69733&sectionno=131&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `All records kept under this Act shall be open to public`
  line `inspection at such times, and on such conditions as to fees or otherwise, as the Chief Commissioner from`
  line `time to time directs.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (69785)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 132
  title `Purposes for which, when settlement is not in progress, Deputy Commissioner shall exercise Settlement-officers’ powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69785&sectionno=132&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `The Deputy Commissioner shall, when a settlement is not in progress,`
  line `exercise the powers conferred by this Act on Settlement-officers for the following purposes:—`
  line
  line `(a) causing boundary-marks to be erected· or repaired, and recovering the. cost of such erection`
  line `and repair;`
  line
  line `(b) assessing land-revenue on lands which are liable to assessment, but have not been assessed;`
  line
  line `(c) declaring any. local area to be a mahal;`
  line
  line `(d) settling lands from which the proprietors were excluded at settlement and to which they have`
  line `been or are about to be re-admitted;`
  line
  line `(e) settling mahals in respect of which an application has been made under the third proviso to`
  line `section fifty-six;`
  line
  line `(f) dealing with claims to hold land wholly or partially free from revenue as against the malguzars;`
  line
  line `(g) assessing lands gained by alluvion;`
  line
  line `(h) ascertaining and recording village-cesses which are levied when this Act comes into force, but`
  line `have not been recorded at the settlement`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (69735)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 133
  title `Purposes for which officers may be invested with Settlement-officers’ powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69735&sectionno=133&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `The Chief`
  line `Commissioner may, during the currency of a settlement, invest any officer with the powers conferred on a`
  line `Settlement-officer by sections forty, forty-one and forty-two; or,`
  line
  line `with the sanction of the Governor General in Council, with any other of the powers which are by this`
  line `Act conferred on a Settlement-officer; but not so as to enable him to enhance the amount of an assessment`
  line `in force under section fifty-six.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (69736)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 134
  title `Cognizance of, and penalty for, offence of injuring boundary-marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69736&sectionno=134&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `Any person wilfully`
  line `erasing, removing or damaging a boundary-mark may be ordered by the Deputy Commissioner or by a`
  line `Tahsildar or naib Tahsildar empowered by the Chief Commissioner in this behalf to pay to the officer`
  line `making the order, in addition to any fine to which such person would be liable under section 434 of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code, such sum, not exceeding fifty rupees, as may in the opinion of such officer be necessary`
  line `to defray the expense of restoring the same, and of rewarding the person (if any) who gave information of`
  line `such erasure, removal or damage.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (69737)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 135
  title `Procedure when person injuring cannot be found.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69737&sectionno=135&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the person erasing, removing`
  line `or damaging such mark cannot be discovered, or if for any other reason it is found impracticable to recover`
  line `from him the sum which he has been ordered to pay, the mark shall be re-erected or repaired at the cost of`
  line `the proprietors, mortgagees or framers of such one or more of the adjoining lands as the Deputy`
  line `Commissioner thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (69738)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 136
  title `Partition of a mahal into two mahals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69738&sectionno=136&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `Any malguzars of a mahal who are not co-sharers with`
  line `the malguzars of such mahal in any lands comprised in such mahal, except such lands as are under the law`
  line `relating to partition the time being in force indivisible, may apply to the Deputy Commissioner to make the`
  line `lands held by them separately from such other malguzars a separate mahal; and the Deputy Commissioner`
  line `shall thereupon make such lands and the lands held separately by the remaining malguzars separate mahals,`
  line `and shall, with the previous sanction of the Commissioner, apportion between the two new mahals thus`
  line `constituted the entire revenue assessed upon the original mahal.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (69739)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 137
  title `Power to make rules as to officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69739&sectionno=137&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may make rules regulating the`
  line `appointment, remuneration, suspension and removal of lambardars, sub-lambardars and mukaddams:`
  line `Provided that, except with the previous sanction of the Governor General in Council, proprietors, other`
  line `than malik-makbuzas, shall not be liable to pay, on account of the aggregate remuneration of lambardars or`
  line `sub-lambardars and mukaddams, a sum exceeding five per cent. on the land-revenue which is assessed on`
  line `their land, or which, when their land is free from revenue, would, in the judgment of the Deputy`
  line `Commissioner, be assessed on their land if it were subject to assessment.`
  line
  line `In framing rules for the appointment under this section of lambardars and sub-lambardars for any mahal,`
  line `the Chief Commissioner shall have regard among other matters to local custom and hereditary claims, and`
  line `to entries on the subject in the record-of-rights of such mahal.`
  line
  line `In every village in which there are resident malguzars, one of such malguzars shall be the mukaddam.`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (69740)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 138
  title `Duties of lambardars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69740&sectionno=138&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of every lambardar and sub-lambardar—`
  line
  line `(a) to collect and pay into the Government Treasury so much of the land-revenue as may under`
  line `section seventy-one be payable through him, either solely or jointly with other lambardars or`
  line sub-lambadars;
  line
  line `(b) to collect and pay to the mukaddam, or into the Government Treasury, as the Deputy`
  line `Commissioner may direct, all sums of money payable through him, either solely or jointly with other`
  line `lambardars or sub-lambardars, by the proprietors whom he represents, on account of the remuneration`
  line `of the mukaddam, patwaris or village-watchmen, or on account of any expenses which the mukaddam`
  line `is authorized to recover from the lambardars or sub-lambardars of his village;`
  line
  line `(c) to assist the mukaddam in obtaining all particulars which he is bound to enter in the annual`
  line `village-papers, or to report under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (69741)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 139
  title `Lambardars may recover fees and other charges from proprietors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69741&sectionno=139&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `Together with the`
  line `land-revenue, lambardars and sub-lambardars may recover from the proprietors whom they respectively`
  line represent—
  line
  line `(a) any remuneration to which they are entitled as such; and`
  line
  line `(b) the sum which, under section one hundred and thirty-eight, they are bound to pay to`
  line `mukaddams:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such recovery shall made from malik-makbuzas paying a percentage which`
  line `includes remuneration to mukaddams and lambardars.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (69742)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 140
  title `Deputy Commissioner may alter channel through which malik-makbuza pays revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69742&sectionno=140&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `On the application of any malik-makbuza or other like holder of land, or of the lambadar or sub-lambardar`
  line `through whom such malik-makbuza or other holder of land pays the revenue assessed on his holding, the`
  line `Deputy Commissioner may, for sufficient cause shown, order that such revenue be paid through any other`
  line `lambardar or sub-lambardar, or that it be paid into the Government Treasury.`
  line
  line `Effect of order for payment of revenue direct to Government.—When the Deputy Commissioner`
  line `orders such payment to be made into the Government Treasury, such portion of the percentage fixed under`
  line `section sixty-four as the Deputy Commissioner, subject to the control of the Chief Commissioner, may`
  line `determine, shall be so paid, and the malik-makbuza or other person shall pay the rest to the mukaddams on`
  line `account of their fees and the other village-expenses.`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (69743)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 141
  title `Duties of mukaddams.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69743&sectionno=141&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of every mukaddam-`
  line
  line `(a) to control and superintend the village-patwari and village-watchmen; to report their deaths or`
  line `absence from duty; to maintain them in the possession of any lands appertaining to their office; to`
  line `recover and pay to them any cash allowances to which they may be entitled; and to take such steps as`
  line `may be necessary to compel them to perform their duties;`
  line
  line `(b) to furnish reports regarding the state of his village, at such places and times as the Deputy`
  line `Commissioner fixes in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) to report and, if possible, to prevent encroachments on the public paths and roadways in his`
  line village;
  line
  line `(d) to preserve such stations and marks erected in his village by Government-surveyors as may be`
  line `made over to his care;`
  line
  line `(e) subject to any rules issued by the Chief Commissioner, to keep his village in good sanitary`
  line condition;
  line
  line `(f) to report violations of any rules which the Chief Commissioner may make for the preservation`
  line `of underwood, forests and trees growing on the village-lands, and for securing to persons entitled to cut`
  line `wood and enjoy other privileges in the waste-lands of the village the rights to which they are entitled;`
  line
  line `(g) to collect, or aid in the collection of, all payments due to Government in his village;`
  line
  line `(h) to report all births and deaths taking place in his village.`
  line
  line `The Chief Commissioner may make rules-`
  line
  line `(1) adding to the list of duties which a mukaddam is required to perform under this section; and`
  line
  line `(2) regulating the liability of persons residing in any village for charges necessarily incurred by`
  line `mukaddams in the performance of the duties specified in clause (e) in respect of such village, and for`
  line `apportioning such charges among such persons; and`
  line
  line `(3) determining the officers to whom reports under this section shall be made`
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (69744)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 142
  title `Liabilities imposed by law on landholders to attach to mukaddams.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69744&sectionno=142&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `When, by any`
  line `enactment for the time being in force, any public duties are imposed on, or public liabilities are declared to`
  line `attach to, landholders, their managers and agents and the like, such duties shall be deemed to be imposed`
  line `on, and such liabilities shall be held to attach to,`
  line `mukaddams appointed under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing herein contained shall discharge landholders, their managers or agents, or the`
  line `like, from any liabilities imposed upon them by law.`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (69745)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 143
  title `Power of mukaddams to recover certain expenses incurred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69745&sectionno=143&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `Every mukaddam may recover`
  line `from the lambardars or sub-lambardars of the village to which he is appointed his own remuneration,`
  line `together with any expenses necessarily incurred in the performance of his duties`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (69746)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 144
  title `Chief Commissioner may make rules as to patwaris.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69746&sectionno=144&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may make`
  line rules-
  line
  line `(a) regulating the manner in which patwaris are to be selected; prescribing the conditions under`
  line `which they may be appointed; and fixing the limits of their circles and the nature, mode and amount of`
  line `their remuneration;`
  line
  line `(b) prescribing the conditions under which substitutes may be appointed for persons having`
  line `hereditary claims to the office of patwari, when such persons are unable to act;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribing the fines which may be imposed on patwaris and their substitutes for neglect of their`
  line `duty, and stating the circumstances under`
  line `which they may be suspended or removed:`
  line
  line `Provided that, except with the previous sanction of the Governor General in Council, no proprietor shall`
  line `be compelled to pay as remuneration to patwaris a sum exceeding six per cent. on the revenue for the time`
  line `being assessed on his land, or which, when his land is free from revenue, would, in the judgment of the`
  line `Deputy Commissioner, be assessable on his land if it were liable to assessment.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (69747)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 145
  title `Chief Commissioner may make rules for guidance of Deputy Commissioner in certain matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69747&sectionno=145&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may make rules for the guidance of Deputy Commissioners in dealing`
  line `with cases where, at the time of making the settlement next before this Act comes into force, the`
  line `maintenance of patwari was made optional, and the persons settled with are unable to agree as to whether`
  line `a patwari should be maintained, and for dealing with cases where no patwari is, under such option,`
  line `maintained and the mukaddams proprietors have made default in the performance of the duties of a patwari.`
  line
  line `Such rules may empower the Deputy Commissioner, in the latter class of cases—`
  line
  line `(a) to impose fines not exceeding fifty rupees on such mukaddams or proprietors, and therefrom to`
  line `make provision for the temporary performance of the duties in respect of which they have made default;`
  line
  line `(b) to appoint patwaris in the villages of such proprietors, either for the term of the settlement or`
  line `for any shorter term, and to fix the remuneration of such patwaris.`
  line `Nothing in the proviso to section one hundred and forty-four shall apply to patwaris so appointed.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (69748)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 146
  title `Chief Commissioner may define duties of patwaris.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69748&sectionno=146&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may make rules`
  line `prescribing the duties of patwaris`
  line
  line `(a) towards the Government; and may in such rules determine the registers, returns or other papers`
  line `which they shall keep or furnish, the forms and language in which such registers and returns are to be`
  line `prepared, the mode of their preparation and attestation, and the dates on which they are to be furnished;`
  line
  line `(b) towards the members of the village-community; and may in such rules fix the remuneration,`
  line `if any, other than the fixed emoluments of their office, which the patwaris may demand in respect of`
  line `the performance of such duties.`
  line
  line `Patwaris papers to be public documents.-All records and papers which patwaris are required to`
  line `prepare or keep by any rule made by the Chief Commissioner under this section shall be deemed to be`
  line `public documents within the meaning of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872, and to be the property of`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (69749)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 147
  title `Patwaris to produce papers for inspection, and to allow copies to be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69749&sectionno=147&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `Patwaris shall`
  line `produce at all reasonable times, for the inspection of all persons interested therein, all records and papers`
  line `which they are so required to prepare or keep, and shall allow such persons to make copies of such records`
  line `and papers.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (69750)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 148
  title `Existing officers confirmed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69750&sectionno=148&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `All existing lambardars, sub-Iambardars, mukaddams and`
  line `patwaris shall, unless the Chief Commissioner in any specified case otherwise directs, be deemed to have`
  line `been appointed under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (69751)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 149
  title `Lambardars’ and other officers’ dues recoverable as arrears.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69751&sectionno=149&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `Any sums which lambardars,`
  line `sub-Iambardars, mukaddams and patwaris are entitled to recover or demand under this chapter may, if the`
  line `Deputy Commissioner so directs, be recovered in the same manner as an arrear of revenue payable directly`
  line `to the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (69752)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 150
  title `Holders of sir-land in Sambalpur to provide for remuneration of mukaddams.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69752&sectionno=150&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `In each`
  line `village of the district of Sambalpur all persons holding sir-land, other than mukaddams, are bound to`
  line `provide for the due remuneration of the mukaddam of the village; and the Chief Commissioner may make`
  line `rules for the enforcement of this obligation`
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (69755)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 151
  title `Right to mines and quarries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69755&sectionno=151&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `Unless it is otherwise expressly provided in the records of a`
  line `settlement or by the terms of a grant made by the Government, the right to all mines, minerals, coals and`
  line `quarries, and to all fisheries in navigable rivers, and the right to extract sap from all palmyra and cocoanut`
  line `trees, shall be deemed to belong to Government; and the Government shall have all powers necessary for`
  line `the proper enjoyment of such rights:`
  line
  line `Provided that, whenever in the exercise by the Government of the rights herein referred to over any`
  line `land, the rights of any persons are infringed by the occupation or disturbance of the surface of such land,`
  line `the Government shall pay to such persons compensation for such infringement, and the amount of such`
  line `compensation shall be determined as nearly as may be in accordance with the provisions of the Land`
  line `Acquisition Act, 1870.`
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (69756)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 152
  title `Exclusive jurisdiction of Revenue-authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69756&sectionno=152&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `Except as otherwise hereinbefore provided,—`
  line
  line `(a) no Civil Court shall entertain any suit instituted, or application made, to obtain a decision or order`
  line `on any matter which the Governor General in Council, the Chief Commissioner or a Revenue or Settlementofficer is, by this Act, empowered to determine or dispose of; and in particular`
  line
  line `(b) no Civil Court shall exercise jurisdiction over any of the following matters:`
  line
  line `(1) any matters provided for in sections forty, forty-one, forty-two and eighty-nine, as to wastelands:`
  line
  line `(2) the claim of any person to have an assessment offered to, or sub-settlement made with, him:`
  line
  line `(3) the amount of revenue or rate to be assessed on any mahal, share or portion of a mahal under`
  line `this or any other Act for the time being in force:`
  line
  line `(4) questions as to the validity of any engagement with Government for the payment of land`
  line `revenue, or of any agreement entered into by superior or inferior proprietors in a settlement or`
  line `sub-settlement:`
  line
  line `(5) claims connected with or arising out of any process enforced on account of refusal to accept the`
  line `assessment offered in a settlement or sub-settlement by the Settlement-officer or Deputy`
  line `Commissioner:`
  line
  line `(6) the amount of the allowance or rent fixed under section sixty-one or sixty-two:`
  line
  line `(7) the redistribution according to established custom, by a Settlement-officer, of land comprised`
  line `in a mahal:`
  line
  line `(8) the formation of the record-of-rights, the preparation, signing or attestation of any of the`
  line `documents contained therein, or the notification of settlement:`
  line
  line `(9) any matters provided for or referred to in sections seventy-three, seventy-four or one hundred`
  line `and thirty as to lands held or claimed to be he1d free from revenue, except rights arising under any`
  line `contract between the Government of India and grantees of land:`
  line
  line `(10) claims connected with, or arising out of, the collection of revenue, or any process enforced on`
  line `account of an arrear of revenue, or on account of any sum which is under this or any other Act realizable`
  line `as revenue:`
  line
  line `(11) claims to set aside, on any ground other than fraud, sales for arrears of revenue:`
  line
  line `(12) corrections of entries revisions of records under sections one hundred and twenty, one hundred`
  line `and twenty-one and one hundred and twenty-two:`
  line
  line `(13) claims to have a partition and apportionment made under section one hundred and thirty-six,`
  line `and questions as to the distribution or apportionment under that section of the land or of the revenue of`
  line `a mahal:`
  line
  line `(14) claims to the office of patwari, lambardar, sub-lambardar or mukaddam, or in respect of any`
  line `injury caused by exclusion therefrom, or to compel the performance of the duties thereof:`
  line
  line `(15) claims to compel the performance of any duties imposed by this Act on any Revenue or`
  line Settlement-officer.
  line
  line `In all the above cases jurdisdiction shall rest with the Revenue-authorities only`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (69757)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 153
  title `For what village-cesses suit lies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69757&sectionno=153&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `No suit shall lie in any Civil or Revenue Court for the recovery`
  line `of any village-cess which has not been sanctioned by the Chief Commissioner and also either recorded at a`
  line `settlement or under section one hundred and thirty-two, clause (h).`
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (69758)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 154
  title `Limitation of claims for composition in case of waste-land demarcated as property of Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69758&sectionno=154&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `Whenever, at any settlement made before this Act comes into force, waste-1ands have been`
  line `demarcated as the property of Government, no claim of any person to, or in respect of, such lands shall be`
  line `entertained by any Civil Court after the expiration of three years from the date of such demarcation.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (69759)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 155
  title `Restriction on Revenue and Settlement-officers trading and holding land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69759&sectionno=155&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `No Revenue or`
  line `Settlement-officer, and no person employed in any Revenue or Settlement office, shall, except with the`
  line `express permission of the Chief Commissioner,—`
  line
  line `(a) engage in trade, or be in any way concerned, directly or indirectly, in any commercial`
  line `transaction, or in the purchase or hiring of land, in the district to which he is appointed, or in which he`
  line `is employed;`
  line
  line `(b) purchase or bid for, either in person or by agent, in his own name or in that of another, or jointly`
  line `or in shares with others, any property which may be sold by order of any Revenue-authority in such`
  line district.
  line
  line `The Chief Commissioner may delegate to Commissioners of divisions or to Deputy Commissioners the`
  line `power of granting the permission mentioned in this section in the case of any specified class of officers.`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section shall be deemed to preclude any person from becoming a member of a company`
  line `incorporated under the Indian Companies Act, 1866.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (69789)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 156
  title `When mahal managed or farmed, or upon proclamation under section 98 or 103, rent payable to Deputy Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69789&sectionno=156&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `When any`
  line `mahal is managed or let in farm under section fifty-seven or fifty-eight, or when either of the proclamations`
  line `mentioned in sections ninety-eight and one hundred and three has been made, all sums due to the proprietor`
  line `in respect of the mahal, share or land mentioned in any of the said sections shall be payable only to the`
  line `Deputy Commissioner or Settlement-officer, his agent or lessee; and no payment made to such proprietor`
  line `in anticipation of the usual period for such payment shall, without the sanction of the Deputy Commissioner`
  line `or Settlement-officer, be credited to the person making the same in account with the Deputy Commissioner`
  line `or Settlement-officer, his agent or lessee.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (69761)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 157
  title `Recovery of balances due by farmers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69761&sectionno=157&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `When any land has been let in farm under the provisions`
  line `of this Act, any revenue due from the farmer in respect of such land may be recovered from him or his`
  line `surety as an arrear of revenue payable directly to Government`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (69762)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 158
  title `Recovery of revenue due when Act comes into force; and of money payable under Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69762&sectionno=158&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line All
  line `land-revenue due when this Act comes into force, and all penalties or other moneys payable to, or`
  line `recoverable by, an officer of Government under this Act, shall be recovered from the persons from whom`
  line `they are due and from the sureties if any of such persons as if such land-revenue, penalties or moneys were`
  line `an arrear of revenue payable directly to Government due under this Act by such persons and their sureties.`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (69763)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 159
  title `Past proceedings for collection of revenue legalized.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69763&sectionno=159&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `All proceedings taken before this Act`
  line `comes into force for the collection of the land-revenue or the realization of arrears thereof shall be deemed`
  line `to have been taken in accordance with law.`
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (69764)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 160
  title `Chief Commissioner may empower persons by name, or confer powers on classes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69764&sectionno=160&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line In
  line `conferring powers under this Act the Chief Commissioner may empower persons by name or classes of`
  line `officials generally by their official titles.`
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (69765)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 161
  title `Chief Commissioner may vary or cancel orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69765&sectionno=161&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may vary or cancel`
  line `any order conferring powers under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (69766)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 162
  title `Chief Commissioner may make rules and attach penalty to breach thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281&sectionId=69766&sectionno=162&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00108_188118_1666091160281
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `The Chief`
  line `Commissioner may, with the previous sanction of the Governor General in Council, make rules consistent`
  line `with this Act for carrying out its provisions, and may attach to the breach of any such rule, or of any other`
  line `rule made by him under this Act, a penalty which may extend to two hundred rupees, or, when such breach`
  line `is a continuing breach, to fifty rupees for each day during which such breach continues.`
  line
  line `All powers to make rules conferred by this Act on the Chief Commissioner shall be exercised subject`
  line `to the control of the Governor General in Council, and may be exercised from time to time as occasion`
  line requires.
  line
  line `No rule made by the Chief Commissioner under this Act shall take effect until it has been published in`
  line `the local official Gazette.`
  line
  line `All such rules, when so published, shall have the force of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
  string
  line
